What i did:-
a> Installed the required package (zip but first saw the hostui for package managers)
b> Created the script - Location (/scripts/news_archive.sh)
Contents:
#!/bin/bash
zip -r /archives/xfusioncorp_news.zip /var/www/html/news
scp /archives/xfusioncorp_news.zip natasha@ststor01:/archives/
these commands do :-
zip -r
zip → creates a ZIP archive.
-r → recursively include all files and subdirectories.
scp
Securely copies files over SSH.

c> Made the script executable : chmod +x /scripts/news_archive.sh
d> Set up passwordless SSH - Switched to the correct user: su -steve
Generated SSH keys: ssh-keygen -t rsa -N "" -f ~/.ssh/id_rsa 
this created private key and public key

e> copied the public key to the Storage Server (ssh-copy-id natasha@ststor01)
added Steve's public key to: 
~natasha/.ssh/authorized_keys on ststor01

THIS RESULTED in SCP and SSH no longer asks for passwords.

f> Tested everything - Ran - /scripts/news_archive.sh
Verified that - ZIP existed on App Server 2 (/archives/xfusioncorp_news.zip)
              - The ZIP also existed on Storage Server (/archives/xfusioncorp_news.zip)

