Key Concepts:
Bash Script → Automates a sequence of Linux commands.
zip → Compresses files/directories into a .zip archive.
scp → Copies files securely between servers using SSH.
SSH Key Authentication → Enables passwordless login by trusting a public key.
chmod +x → Makes a script executable.
su - steve → Switches to the user who is supposed to run the script.
Why no sudo in scripts?
Scripts should run with the permissions of the intended user and not rely on interactive privilege escalation.

Automated the backup of a website directory by zipping it, storing it locally, and securely transferring it to another server using passwordless SSH
